pesto chicken
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fqLZ5Wmf9YE

2 chicken breasts, sliced into ½-inch strips
2 tablespoons garlic, chopped
	4 cloves
½ tablespoon kosher salt
½ tablespoon freshly ground black pepper
¾ cup heavy cream
	200g
½ grated parmesan cheese
	45g => 50g
¼ cup pesto
	90ml is enough.
3 cups penne pasta, cooked and drained
	300g-400g depends on needs.
¾ cup cherry tomatoes, halved


add olive oii to pan and cook 2 chicken breasts. (thin them out)
	remove when nearly done
		meanwhile pasta
chop 4 garlics (or use mixer) and add them to pan
	meanwhile cut chicken into pieces
slow down fire	
	add pepper
	add cream
	add parmesan
	add pesto
	add chicken cubes
	add pasta.